Refine audit log and payment statistics queries in ApiController
Updated the ApiController to enhance the audit() function to filter logs based on the user's name and limit the data to the most recent 15 records. Simplified the paymentStatistics() function to calculate paid, refunded, and disputed payments for the current month and year only, instead of a flexible period defined by query parameters. These changes will improve the application's performance and data accuracy for audit logs and payment statistics.

Replace Quill input with Input in EventsEditScreen and add FCM notification on login
Replaced Quill input type with standard Input in EventsEditScreen.php for better readability and ease of use. In LoginController.php, added a line to send Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) notifications to the user when a new login is detected. This enhancement improves the security by alerting users about their account usage in real time.

Revise event filtering and formatting in ApiController
Updated ApiController to filter events based on their type and status, ensuring only 'PHYSICAL', 'INCOMING' and 'STARTED' events are retrieved. Expanded time formatting of events to include month and year, and improved handling of missing city information. The changes enhance the specificity and completeness of the event data retrieved.

Implemented loading, error, and data states in AkceCalendar component
In this commit, we've added different UI states to the AkceCalendar component.
- Loading state: When the data is being fetched, a CircularProgressIndicator is shown. - Error state: If there's an error while fetching the data, an error message is displayed on the screen. - Data state: Upon successful data fetching, the data is displayed in a list.
These UI states are managed with Composable functions and mutableStateOf variables, and fetching simulation is done via a LaunchedEffect block.
This improvement enhances the user experience by properly managing and communicating the application's state during data fetching.
